= La calificación

On the first of September, Miguel de la Madrid rises for his final Informe — and cannot finish a paragraph: from the opposition benches, for the first time in the institution's history, a president of the Republic is interrupted, heckled, interpellated to his face by deputies waving actas. Muñoz Ledo stands to challenge him directly; the old deputies look physically ill; the broadcast, live, cannot be uninvented.

Days later the Chamber, sitting as electoral college with its PRI majority, qualifies the election of Carlos Salinas — over the opposition's walkout, over the sealed ballot packets that will be guarded like plutonium and eventually burned. The legal road ends here, at a locked and voted door.

- @constancia: Read the full documentation into the record first — every casilla, every acta, three hours of arithmetic aloud, so the burning later will burn a copy.

